  "body": "The Hardhat config file format has a section for configuring Hardhat Network. Rethnet's JSON-RPC server CLI should support the same configuration functionality.\r\n\r\nWhile Hardhat can support config files as either JavaScript or TypeScript files, for simplicity `rethnet` will only support a JSON file.\r\n\r\n**Definition of Done**\r\n- The `rethnet` crate should include a serde-compatible specification of all of the functionality documented at https://hardhat.org/hardhat-network/docs/reference#config\r\n- At startup, the `rethnet node` command should read a config file `rethnet.config.json`, parse it according to the aforementioned spec, and apply that configuration according to the rethnet functionality existing at the time of implementation.\r\n  - The use of any config functionality that is NOT supported by rethnet at the time of implementation should result in an error or warning (`unimplemented!()`?)\r\n- The `DEFAULT_ACCOUNTS` variable in the `rethnet` crate should be replaced with a representation more integrated with this holistic approach.",
